N,N,N'-trimethyl-N'-(1H-pyrrol-2-yl)ethane-1,2-diamine can be represented as (CH3)3N(C4H8N)N(CH2)2NH2. 

By analyzing the molecular formula, we can determine the number of atoms in the compound:

3 atoms in each methyl group (3 x 3 = 9 atoms)
4 atoms in the pyrrol group (4 atoms)
2 atoms in the ethane group (2 atoms)
1 atom in the amine group (1 atom)

Thus, the total number of atoms in N,N,N'-trimethyl-N'-(1H-pyrrol-2-yl)ethane-1,2-diamine is 16 atoms.
